CHRISTMAS LEFTOVER KOTHU ROTI 

Kothu Roti isn't just the ultimate street food dish in Sri Lanka, but also a terrific way to use up leftovers. The story goes that this dish was invented by someone returning home hungry from a big night out, raiding their fridge and tossing it all up together in a wok. 

You can do the same with leftover greens, meat, eggs, etc after your Christmas dinner, bringing it all together with some chopped up rotis (you can use frozen rotis or parathas, or even chopped up tortillas) and curry (ideally something Sri Lankan or South Indian). 

The list and quantities of ingredients are totally up to you, feel free to get creative! We'd love to see what you get up to, so don't forget to tag us in your pictures.

